    {
      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "The fight of organized labor against\nthe Hotel Butler began last summer,\nwhen the hotel was being remodeled\nby the company that opened it.\n\n\nThe question was one that was ex-\npected to be brought before the meet\ning of the State Federation of Labor,\nbut both factions allowed that meet\ning 10 pass without bringing up the\nsubject. Since that time the boycott\nof the unions against the Seattle\nBrewing & Mailing company has been\nin effect, but the public has gradually\nlost sight of the fight"
    }
